/*Flow per iteration
1️⃣ Add number to running sum
sum += num
2️⃣ Check if a previous sum makes a subarray = k
if (map.containsKey(sum - k))
If true → increase count
If false → do nothing
3️⃣ Regardless of the if, store the current sum
map.put(sum, ...)
1. Update running sum
2. Check if (sum - k) exists → increase count
3. Record this sum in map */

            int sum=0;
            int count = 0;
            int target=1;
            int arr1[] = {0,1,2};

            Map<Integer,Integer> map= new HashMap<>();
            map.put(0,1);
            for(int i =0; i < arr1.length; i++)
            {
                
                sum+=arr1[i];
                if(map.containsKey(sum-target))
                {
                   count+=map.get(sum-target);

                }
                map.put(sum, map.getOrDefault(sum,0) +1);
